{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~kobsa/courses/ICS104/course-notes/colors-recommended.htm", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//w3c//dtd html 4.0 transitional//en\">\n<html><head>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n   <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\">\n   <meta name=\"GENERATOR\" content=\"Mozilla/4.72 (Macintosh; I; PPC) [Netscape]\"><title>Recommendable usage of colors</title></head><body bgcolor=\"#ffffff\">\n<big><font style=\"font-weight: bold;\" face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><big>Recommendable usage of colors</big></font></big> \n<ul>\n <li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Emphasis</b> \n(particularly when used as background)</font></li><li> \n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Grouping or separating neighboring objects</b></font><font size=\"+3\"><font style=\"font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;\"><br>\n (particularly when used as background)</font>&nbsp;</font></li> \n<li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Coding of discrete data</b></font></li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"> \n</font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\">(not more than 7+/-2 colors \nif codes have to be remembered)</font> <li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Window \nsystems</b>: marking the type of window or application</font></li><li> \n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Graphics</b>: Visual separation of overlapping \ngraphical elements or labels</font></li>\n  <li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Naturalness \nin photorealistic images</b></font></li>\n  <li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Warnings, status reports</b></font></li>\n<li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Depth \nin 3-D graphics</b></font></li>\n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"> (reddish \ncolors appear closer, blueish colors more distant)</font> \n\n<li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><b>Coding \nof continuous data</b> in information landscapes </font></li>\n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\">(e.g., \nfalse color representation)</font><font size=\"+3\"> </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"false-color1.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" alt=\"The linked image shows a jet fighter in false colors encoding different degrees of pressure\" border=\"0\" height=\"11\" width=\"11\"></a></font></font><font size=\"+3\"> \n  </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"false-color3.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" alt=\"The linked image shows a mountain range in false colors\" border=\"0\" height=\"11\" width=\"11\"></a></font></font><font size=\"+3\"> \n  </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"+3\"><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"false-color4.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" alt=\"The linked image shows an underwater topology off Boston, MA with false colors encoding different depth levels\" border=\"0\" height=\"11\" width=\"11\"></a></font></font> \n<li> \n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"5\"><font size=\"+3\"><b>To increase the attractiveness of an \ninterface</b>, following guidelines for color selection <font size=\"+2\">(increased attractiveness \ndoes not necessarily imply an increase in usability</font></font><font size=\"+2\">)</font></font></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n</body></html>", "encoding": "ascii"}